## Components

### One component per file
No exceptions. Each component has its own file.

### Component files always export one thing — the component
```tsx
// UserVoiceBubble.tsx
export function UserVoiceBubble({ message }: UserVoiceBubbleProps) {
  // ...
}
```

No default exports. Named exports only — easier to refactor, easier to find.

### Props interfaces are defined in the same file, above the component
```tsx
interface UserVoiceBubbleProps {
  message: VoiceMessage
  onTranscribe: (messageId: string) => void
}

export function UserVoiceBubble({ message, onTranscribe }: UserVoiceBubbleProps) {
  // ...
}
```

### Component structure — always in this order
```tsx
// 1. Imports
// 2. Types/interfaces
// 3. Constants local to the component (if any)
// 4. The component function
//    a. State
//    b. Refs
//    c. Derived values (useMemo)
//    d. Effects
//    e. Handlers
//    f. Early returns (loading, error, empty)
//    g. Return JSX
// 5. Styles (StyleSheet.create at bottom of file)
```

### Extract sub-components aggressively

If a section of JSX has its own logic or is getting long, it's a component.
Even if it's only used once. Single-use components are fine — they're
documentation. They give a name to a concept.

```tsx
// ✗ Everything in one render
export function MessageList({ messages }: Props) {
  return (
    <FlatList
      data={messages}
      renderItem={({ item }) => (
        <View style={styles.row}>
          {item.role === 'user' ? (
            <View style={styles.userBubble}>
              {item.kind === 'voice' ? (
                // 30 lines of voice bubble...
              ) : (
                // 20 lines of text bubble...
              )}
            </View>
          ) : (
            // 40 lines of pem bubble...
          )}
        </View>
      )}
    />
  )
}

// ✓ Composed from named pieces
export function MessageList({ messages }: Props) {
  return (
    <FlatList
      data={messages}
      renderItem={({ item }) => <MessageRow message={item} />}
      keyExtractor={m => m.id}
    />
  )
}
```

