## DRY — Don't Repeat Yourself

### If you write the same thing twice, extract it
```typescript
// ✗ Repeated
const isOverdue = task.dueAt < new Date() && task.status !== 'done'
// ...50 lines later...
if (task.dueAt < new Date() && task.status !== 'done') { ... }

// ✓ Extracted once
import { isOverdue } from '@/utils/isOverdue'
```

### Magic values become constants
```typescript
// ✗ Magic values scattered in code
if (messages.length > 50) loadMore()
setTimeout(retry, 3000)

// ✓ Named constants
const MESSAGES_PER_PAGE = 50
const RETRY_DELAY_MS = 3000

if (messages.length > MESSAGES_PER_PAGE) loadMore()
setTimeout(retry, RETRY_DELAY_MS)
```

### Constants live in `constants/` or at the top of the file they belong to
```
constants/
  chat.constants.ts
  tasks.constants.ts
  api.constants.ts
```

