## NestJS backend specifics

### Controllers are thin — they only route
```typescript
// ✓ Thin controller
@Controller('chat')
export class ChatController {
  constructor(private readonly chatService: ChatService) {}

  @Post('messages')
  async sendMessage(
    @Body() dto: SendMessageDto,
    @GetUser() user: AuthUser,
  ) {
    return this.chatService.sendMessage(user.id, dto)
  }
}

// ✗ Fat controller — business logic does not belong here
@Post('messages')
async sendMessage(@Body() dto: SendMessageDto, @GetUser() user: AuthUser) {
  const message = await this.db.messages.create({ data: { ...dto, userId: user.id } })
  const intent = await this.openai.classify(dto.content)
  await this.queue.add('process-message', { messageId: message.id, intent })
  return { messageId: message.id, status: 'received' }
}
```

### Services have one responsibility
If a service file is doing classification AND embedding AND sending SSE events,
split it.

```
chat/
  chat.controller.ts
  chat.service.ts          ← orchestrates, delegates
  chat.module.ts
  services/
    classify-intent.service.ts   ← only classification
    embed-message.service.ts     ← only embedding
    sse.service.ts               ← only SSE
  jobs/
    process-dump.job.ts
    transcribe-voice.job.ts
    embed-message.job.ts
  dto/
    send-message.dto.ts
    paginate-messages.dto.ts
```

### Extract single-purpose functions from services
```typescript
// ✓ Single purpose, easy to test
// classify-intent.ts
export async function classifyIntent(content: string): Promise<Intent> {
  const result = await generateText({
    model: openai('gpt-4o-mini'),
    output: Output.choice({ options: ['dump', 'command', 'question'] }),
    prompt: buildClassifyPrompt(content),
  })
  return result.output
}
```

Use **`generateText` + `Output.*`** per **`pem-core-loop.mdc`** — not `generateObject` / `streamObject`.

### DTOs validate at the boundary — always use class-validator
```typescript
export class SendMessageDto {
  @IsEnum(['text', 'voice'])
  kind: 'text' | 'voice'

  @IsString()
  @IsOptional()
  content?: string

  @IsUrl()
  @IsOptional()
  voiceUrl?: string
}
```

### No raw SQL in services — use Drizzle query builder
```typescript
// ✓ Drizzle
const messages = await db
  .select()
  .from(messagesTable)
  .where(and(eq(messagesTable.userId, userId), lt(messagesTable.createdAt, before)))
  .orderBy(desc(messagesTable.createdAt))
  .limit(50)

// ✗ Raw SQL in application code
const messages = await db.query(`SELECT * FROM messages WHERE user_id = $1...`)
```

