## React Native specifics

### StyleSheet.create always at bottom of component file
```typescript
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    flex: 1,
    backgroundColor: colors.bg,
  },
  // ...
})
```

### No inline styles except for dynamic values
```tsx
// ✓ Dynamic value inline (changes at runtime)
<View style={{ opacity: progress }} />
<View style={{ height: keyboardHeight }} />

// ✗ Static value inline (should be in StyleSheet)
<View style={{ backgroundColor: '#faf8f4', padding: 16 }} />
```

### Colors, spacing, typography from constants — never hardcoded
```typescript
// constants/theme.ts
export const colors = {
  bg: '#faf8f4',
  amber: '#e8763a',
  amberDark: '#c45e22',
  amberBg: '#fdf2ea',
  text: '#1c1a16',
  text2: '#6b6560',
  muted: '#b8b0a4',
  border: '#e8e2d8',
}

export const spacing = {
  xs: 4,
  sm: 8,
  md: 12,
  lg: 16,
  xl: 24,
  xxl: 32,
}

export const radius = {
  sm: 8,
  md: 12,
  lg: 18,
  full: 999,
}
```

Prefer **`app/constants/theme.ts`** and **`typography.ts`** (Pem brand) over duplicating values.

### No `any` — ever
```typescript
// ✗ any hides bugs
const handleEvent = (event: any) => { ... }

// ✓ type it properly
const handleEvent = (event: GestureResponderEvent) => { ... }
```

### Avoid nested ternaries — maximum one level deep
```tsx
// ✗ Nested ternary — unreadable
{isLoading ? <Spinner /> : hasError ? <ErrorState /> : <Content />}

// ✓ Early returns handle states, ternary only for binary choices
if (isLoading) return <Spinner />
if (hasError) return <ErrorState error={error} />
return <Content />
```

