## Prompts are isolated

AI prompts are first-class code. They live in their own **`.ts` files** next to the code that uses them — typically under **`modules/<feature>/services/`** (e.g. **`pem-agent.system-prompt.ts`**) or as private helpers on an **`@Injectable()`** *Llm* service (e.g. **`ChatQuestionLlmService`**) — not buried inside unrelated orchestration services.

They are functions that take typed inputs and return strings (or are private string builders on an injectable).

```typescript
// services/chat-question-llm.service.ts — excerpt: prompt builder on an @Injectable() service
buildAskQuestionSystemPrompt(nameNote: string): string {
  return `You are Pem — a friend who remembers everything.${nameNote} …`.trim()
}
```

Avoid embedding huge prompt strings in service files — **extract** when adding or refactoring (existing **`pem-agent.service.ts`** may be grandfathered until split per line limits).

