## Security — non-negotiable, always on

Security is not a feature you add later. It is part of every line of code.
Every endpoint, every query, every environment variable.
If you are writing code that touches user data and security is not in your head, stop.

### Authentication — always verify, never trust

Every endpoint is protected by Clerk auth unless explicitly marked public.
Never write an endpoint without the auth guard. Never.

```typescript
// ✓ Every protected endpoint
@UseGuards(ClerkAuthGuard)
@Controller('chat')
export class ChatController { ... }

// ✓ Explicit public endpoints only
@Public()
@Get('health')
healthCheck() { return { status: 'ok' } }
```

Never trust user-provided IDs. Always derive the user ID from the verified auth token.

```typescript
// ✗ Never — user controls their own userId
@Get('messages')
getMessages(@Body('userId') userId: string) { ... }

// ✓ Always — userId comes from verified token only
@Get('messages')
getMessages(@GetUser() user: AuthUser) {
  return this.chatService.getMessages(user.id)
}
```

### Data isolation — every query scopes to the authenticated user

Never query without a userId filter. A user must never be able to
access another user's data — not through ID manipulation, not through
any endpoint.

```typescript
// ✗ Missing user scope — any user can see any message
const message = await db.select().from(messages).where(eq(messages.id, messageId))

// ✓ Always scoped — userId from verified token, not from request
const message = await db
  .select()
  .from(messages)
  .where(and(
    eq(messages.id, messageId),
    eq(messages.userId, authenticatedUserId), // ← always
  ))

if (!message) throw new NotFoundException()
```

Make this a habit: every single db query that returns user data must filter by userId.

### Input validation — validate everything at the boundary

All incoming data is validated at the DTO level before it touches a service.
Never pass raw request body to a service.

```typescript
// ✓ Validate at the edge
export class SendMessageDto {
  @IsEnum(['text', 'voice'])
  kind: 'text' | 'voice'

  @IsString()
  @MaxLength(10000)        // ← always set max lengths
  @IsOptional()
  content?: string

  @IsUrl({ protocols: ['https'] })  // ← https only
  @IsOptional()
  voiceUrl?: string
}
```

### Environment variables — never in code, never in logs

```typescript
// ✗ Hardcoded secrets
const apiKey = 'sk-proj-abc123...'

// ✓ Always from environment
const apiKey = process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY
if (!apiKey) throw new Error('OPENAI_API_KEY is required')
```

Never log request bodies, tokens, API keys, or any user content.
Logs are observable by people who are not the user.

```typescript
// ✗ Logs user content
console.log('Processing message:', messageContent)
console.log('User token:', authToken)

// ✓ Logs only safe identifiers
this.logger.log(`Processing message ${messageId} for user ${userId}`)
```

### SQL injection — use the query builder, never string interpolation

Drizzle's query builder parameterizes automatically.
Never construct SQL strings with user input.

```typescript
// ✗ SQL injection vector
const result = await db.query(`SELECT * FROM messages WHERE content LIKE '%${search}%'`)

// ✓ Parameterized via Drizzle
const result = await db
  .select()
  .from(messages)
  .where(like(messages.content, `%${search}%`)) // Drizzle handles escaping
```

### Rate limiting — global guard

Protect against abuse and runaway costs. Use **`ThrottlerModule.forRoot`** in **`app.module.ts`** with **`ThrottlerGuard`** as **`APP_GUARD`** — one default for all routes (e.g. per IP). Do not add **`@Throttle`** or **`@SkipThrottle`** on controllers unless you intentionally introduce exceptions.

```typescript
ThrottlerModule.forRoot([{ ttl: 60_000, limit: 600 }]),
{ provide: APP_GUARD, useClass: ThrottlerGuard },
```

### File uploads — validate type and size

Never trust the Content-Type header. Validate the actual file.

```typescript
// ✓ Validate uploads
const ALLOWED_AUDIO_TYPES = ['audio/m4a', 'audio/mp4', 'audio/webm', 'audio/wav']
const MAX_VOICE_SIZE_BYTES = 25 * 1024 * 1024 // 25MB (Whisper limit)

if (!ALLOWED_AUDIO_TYPES.includes(file.mimetype)) {
  throw new BadRequestException('Invalid audio format')
}
if (file.size > MAX_VOICE_SIZE_BYTES) {
  throw new BadRequestException('File too large')
}
```

### CORS — explicit allowlist, never wildcard in production

```typescript
// ✗ Never in production
app.enableCors({ origin: '*' })

// ✓ Explicit origins only
app.enableCors({
  origin: [process.env.APP_URL, 'https://heypem.com'],
  credentials: true,
})
```

### Security checklist — run through this for every new endpoint

- [ ] Is this endpoint protected by ClerkAuthGuard?
- [ ] Does every DB query filter by `authenticatedUserId`?
- [ ] Is all input validated by a DTO with class-validator?
- [ ] Are max lengths set on all string inputs?
- [ ] Is the endpoint rate-limited?
- [ ] Are there any secrets, tokens, or user content in logs?
- [ ] If file upload: is type and size validated?

