## The checklist before every PR

### Code quality
- [ ] No file exceeds its line limit
- [ ] No ternary with more than one line of JSX on either side
- [ ] No inline styles for static values
- [ ] No hardcoded colors, spacing, or text strings (except in constants files)
- [ ] Every boolean variable starts with is/has/can/should/did
- [ ] Every handler starts with handle
- [ ] No `any` types
- [ ] Every component has a single responsibility
- [ ] Every hook returns only what the component needs
- [ ] AI prompts extracted or justified if embedded (see line limits)
- [ ] Controllers are thin — no business logic
- [ ] No magic numbers — everything is a named constant

### Security
- [ ] Is every new endpoint protected by ClerkAuthGuard?
- [ ] Does every DB query that returns user data filter by authenticatedUserId?
- [ ] Is all input validated by a DTO with class-validator and max lengths?
- [ ] Is the endpoint rate-limited?
- [ ] Are there any secrets, tokens, or user content in logs?
- [ ] If file upload: is type and size validated?

### Scalability
- [ ] Does every new DB query have indexes on all WHERE and ORDER BY fields?
- [ ] Is all data paginated — no unbounded queries?
- [ ] Are slow AI calls in BullMQ jobs, not the request path?
- [ ] Is the service stateless?
